From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Batocera <batocera@localhost>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 14:28:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] qt: do not force portable mode on Linux

NanoBoyAdvance's Qt frontend forces PORTABLE_MODE when it is not built
as a macOS app bundle.  On Batocera that makes the emulator load a
relative config.toml from the process working directory, so the
configgen-created XDG config is ignored and the BIOS path falls back to
bios.bin.

Keep portable mode as an explicit opt-in option so Linux builds use
QStandardPaths and read $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/NanoBoyAdvance/config.toml.
---
 src/platform/qt/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/platform/qt/CMakeLists.txt b/src/platform/qt/CMakeLists.txt
index 8ba63ff..727c6ee 100644
--- a/src/platform/qt/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/platform/qt/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -9 +9 @@
-cmake_dependent_option(PORTABLE_MODE "Enable portable mode" OFF MACOS_BUILD_APP_BUNDLE ON)
+option(PORTABLE_MODE "Enable portable mode" OFF)
